IMDB Ratings

IMDB provides breakdown of votes and ratings per gender and age group (for example see http://www.imdb.com/title/tt2713180/ratings). This data was scraped for all the movies that have more than 10,000 votes (all 5,374 of them!).

Loading packages and data.

## Loading required package: Rcpp
## Loading required package: RColorBrewer

What is the ratio of male/female voters?

## Average number of male voters for a movie:  53708
## Average number of female voters for a movie:  13136
## Ratio of male/female voters:  4.088611

Do men and women rate movies differently?

## Average rating of a movie by male voters:  6.534041
## Average rating of a movie by female voters:  6.671709

Although the difference in rating is only 0.11 out of 10, but women significantly rate movies higher than men (p-value < 0.0001).

So how does age affect the rating?

Clearly the younger generation vote more favorably than the adults!

Are newer movies getting better ratings?

## geom_smooth: method="auto" and size of largest group is >=1000, so using gam with formula: y ~ s(x, bs = "cs"). Use 'method = x' to change the smoothing method.

Apparently not! But does this mean old movies were better? Perhaps not. People might just be nostalgic, and hence biased about them.

Which genres are more prevalent among the highly-voted movies?

If we are not familiar with these movies, we can just look at the genres that are more popular with each gender. Well take the first 100 movies that are more popular with each group, and see what they are. Drama and comedy were removed, as they were both equally popular with men and women.

As expected, women enjoy romance and family movies more than men, and men enjoy crime, thriller, and action movies more. Music and fantasy genre are also more popular with women, probably because of Twilight series and Bieber-type movies that are not very popular with men.

Now, lets take a look at at actors/actresses, and see which ones appear more in the first 250 top-rated movies.

This is not as obvious as the genres graph. I personally expected to see names like Al Pacino, Robert Deniro, and Meryl Strip here, but most of these names are unknown to me. So I looked them up, and realized that they are mostly actors that had uncredited roles in many many movies. So although they appear in many top 250 movies of all times, this does not mean they had central roles!
